# =============================================================================
# Sovereign Network Mobile — Environment Configuration
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
# This is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for all platform configs.
# Run `node scripts/generate-config.js` after changing .env to regenerate
# platform-specific configs (src/config.ts, ios/GeneratedConfig.swift,
# android/.../GeneratedConfig.kt).
# =============================================================================

# --- Node Registry ---
# Comma-separated list of nodes in format: host:port:spki_pin_hex
# The SPKI pin is the Base64-decoded SHA-256 hash of the server's SubjectPublicKeyInfo.
# Generate with: openssl s_client -connect host:port </dev/null 2>/dev/null | openssl x509 -pubkey -noout | openssl pkey -pubin -outform der | openssl dgst -sha256 -binary | base64
ZHTP_NODE_REGISTRY=g1.thesovereignnetwork.org:9334:abc123...,g2.thesovereignnetwork.org:9334:def456...

# --- Default Node (optional) ---
# ZHTP_DEFAULT_NODE=g1.thesovereignnetwork.org:9334

# --- Build Configuration ---
# Set to the path of your local The-Sovereign-Network repository (sibling to this project).
# This is required if you need to rebuild Rust native libraries (QUIC JNI, UHP FFI, etc.).
# THE_SOVEREIGN_NETWORK_PATH=../The-Sovereign-Network
